{"body": "It sounds like a bug in rack-test. That is, browsers eat the first newline inside a textarea tag, so rack-test should respect that behavior and not treat the first newline as part of the actual content.\r\n\r\nBut since Rails hasn't match the way the browser works until now (this bug existed in Rails 1 even is my understanding) I wouldn't be surprised to find that rack-test had been written to match Rails behavior rather than browser behavior.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4841344", "created_at": "2012-03-30T12:19:45Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5191#issuecomment-4841344", "updated_at": "2012-03-30T12:19:45Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 5191, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jcoleman", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/d8d5058aa91cd439f1f486f93f8eb564?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F518fe206be008d8f98488ba515188a69.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/received_events", "gravatar_id": "d8d5058aa91cd439f1f486f93f8eb564", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jcoleman", "type": "User", "id": 125331, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52381b8abd3543c15100e406"}, "id": 4841344, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5191"}
